{
  "text": "There is always a chance of the coexistence of pelvic endometriosis causing pelvic pain. There are no recommendations or guidelines to perform simultaneous laparoscopy to diagnose coexisting pelvic endometriosis while performing a local excision [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "207473341"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "207473341": {
      "title": "Umbilical laparoscopic scar endometriosis",
      "abstract": "Umbilical endometriosis is rare and challenging in both diagnosis and treatment. We report a case of an umbilical scar endometriotic nodule in a 39-year-old lady following laparoscopy-assisted vaginal hysterectomy. The wide local excision of the nodule and histopathological examination confirmed the diagnosis. We discuss the pathogenesis, diagnosis, differential diagnosis, and treatment options for the patient."
    }
  }
}